so you may think it looks nasty and
dirty

00:00:14.219 --> 00:00:18.350
after sitting around all winter buried
in snow and ice and who knows what

00:00:18.350 --> 00:00:21.820
but a few simple things you do the first
thing you want to do

00:00:21.820 --> 00:00:25.330
is turn on the gas light the burners

00:00:25.330 --> 00:00:28.340
set it on high and burn everything off

00:00:28.340 --> 00:00:32.480
for like 15 min up

00:00:32.480 --> 00:00:36.710
turn it on

00:00:36.710 --> 00:00:40.989
put it on high

00:00:40.989 --> 00:00:47.989
light the burners

00:00:57.649 --> 00:01:02.359
open your lid

00:01:02.359 --> 00:01:09.359
take a nice brush

00:01:17.979 --> 00:01:19.860
scrub

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:26.790
if it is icky up here on the lid scrub that off too

00:01:34.850 --> 00:01:36.020
you wanna do this

00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:40.470
every single time you use your  barbecue
heat  it up scrub it all

00:01:40.470 --> 00:01:43.910
until it's clean if it still looks
creepy

00:01:43.910 --> 00:01:50.470
take sudsy water and scrub

00:01:50.470 --> 00:01:54.170
turn off the gas flip your grates over and scrub on

00:01:54.170 --> 00:02:01.170
on the underneath side

00:02:07.190 --> 00:02:14.190
but down on all the  parts  flavor bars

00:02:14.670 --> 00:02:21.670
all of that ash and soot is off

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:30.880
be careful  don't burn yourself

00:02:35.540 --> 00:02:40.000
do it on both sides of all of it

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:42.000
get it as clean as you can

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:43.160
your kitchen floor

00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:46.760
and nobody is going to be judging you
you're just going to be throwing

00:02:46.760 --> 00:02:47.540
food on

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:51.550
cooking it and so don't worry about it
being like completely clean

00:02:51.550 --> 00:02:56.100
then you want to go down look down below
to where the grease catchers are

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:59.870
this one has a big pull out tray and a
left-right so I'm gonna

